    "Deploying a controller in an environment other than the one used in its training resulted in performance losses that might be acceptable depending on the case study.",
    "These losses were higher, and possibly impractical, in agents trained progressively through different climates, showing biases towards the last training environment employed.",
    "One of the main advantages that DRL controllers offer compared to reactive control techniques is their flexibility in customizing the comfort-consumption trade-off by simply altering their reward function.",
